## 15. Security Considerations

|Concern         |Approach                                                                                                                         |
|----------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|Authentication  |JWT via `python-jose`; `require_role("llm_user")` dependency for execution, `require_role("llm_admin")` for checkpoint management|
|API Keys        |Loaded from env vars or HashiCorp Vault via `hvac` — never in source                                                             |
|PII in rules    |`canonical_content` scanned before LLM call; offending fields masked in traces                                                   |
|Prompt injection|Input sanitized before Jinja2 rendering — strips control characters                                                              |
|Audit           |`ExecutionTrace` records are append-only; JWT `sub` (actor) stored on each trace                                                 |
|Rate limiting   |`slowapi` (Starlette middleware, Limits syntax) per API key                                                                      |
|CORS            |Explicit `allow_origins` — no wildcard in staging/prod                                                                           |

